'''城市径流'''（{{lang-en|urban runoff}}）是[[城市化|城市化]]造成雨水的[[地表径流|地表径流]]。这种径流是世界许多城市化地区[[水污染|水污染]]的主要来源。城市径流可能造成[[內澇|內澇]]和城市[[水污染|水污染]]。

[[道路|道路]]、[[停车场|停车场]]和[[人行道|人行道]]等不透水-{表}-面是在土地开发过程中建设形成的。在暴风雨和其他强[[降水|降水]]过程中，这些由[[沥青|沥青]]、[[水泥|水泥]]、[[混凝土|混凝土]]等建造的不透水-{表}-面以及屋顶排水系統会使污水流入[[下水道|下水道]]，而不是让[[土壤|土壤]]对污水进行[[过滤|过滤]]。这会导致[[地下水|地下水]]位的降低（因为地下水的补给减少了）和[[洪水|洪水]]（因为留在地表的水量增加了）。<ref name="ASCE1">[http://wef.org Water Environment Federation,] {{Wayback|url=http://wef.org/ |date=20200906083717 }} Alexandria, VA; and [http://www.asce.org American Society of Civil Engineers,] {{Wayback|url=http://www.asce.org/ |date=20200909191055 }} Reston, VA. [http://books.google.com/books?id=AdU-VXXV_H0C "Urban Runoff Quality Management."] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=AdU-VXXV_H0C |date=20110629122013 }} WEF Manual of Practice No. 23; ASCE Manual and Report on Engineering Practice No. 87. 1998. ISBN 1-57278-039-8. Chapter 1.</ref><ref>Schueler, Thomas R. [http://www.cwp.org/Resource_Library/Center_Docs/PWP/ELC_PWP1.pdf "The Importance of Imperviousness."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cwp.org/Resource_Library/Center_Docs/PWP/ELC_PWP1.pdf |date=20090227110104 }} Reprinted in [http://www.cwp.org/Store/guidance.htm ''The Practice of Watershed Protection.''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cwp.org/Store/guidance.htm |date=20081223004441 }} 2000. Center for Watershed Protection. Ellicott City, MD.</ref> 大多数市的雨水排水系统会将未处理的雨水排入[[溪流|溪流]]、[[江河|江河]]和[[海湾|海湾]]。這些多餘的水還會以通過地下室儲水和渗透建筑物的牆壁和地板進入人們的房舍。

==城市径流中的污染物==
[[Image:Natural_&_impervious_cover_diagrams_EPA.jpg|thumb]]
水流流过这些不透水的表面往往会从道路和停车场冲走[[汽油|汽油]]、[[机油|机油]]、[[重金属|重金属]]、垃圾和其他污染物，从草坪冲走[[化肥|化肥]]和[[农药|农药]]。道路和停车场是[[镍|镍]]、[[铜|铜]]、[[锌|锌]]、[[镉|镉]]、[[铅|铅]]和[[多环芳香烃|多环芳香烃]]（PAHs）的主要来源，这是汽油和其他矿物燃料燃烧所产生的副产品。屋顶雨水内含有大量的[[有机化合物|有机化合物]]与[[锌|锌]]（由镀锌水槽产生）。住宅的草坪、公园和高尔夫球场中使用的化肥是[[硝酸盐|硝酸盐]]和[[磷|磷]]的一个重要来源。<ref name="ASCE1" /><ref>{{cite book|title=Stormwater Effects Handbook: A Toolbox for Watershed Managers, Scientists, and Engineers|authors=G. Allen Burton, Jr., Robert Pitt|publisher=CRC/Lewis Publishers|location=New York|date=2001|isbn=0-87371-924-7|url=http://unix.eng.ua.edu/~rpitt/Publications/BooksandReports/Stormwater%20Effects%20Handbook%20by%20%20Burton%20and%20Pitt%20book/MainEDFS_Book.html|access-date=2009-06-12|archive-date=2009-05-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090519035716/http://unix.eng.ua.edu/~rpitt/Publications/BooksandReports/Stormwater%20Effects%20Handbook%20by%20%20Burton%20and%20Pitt%20book/MainEDFS_Book.html|dead-url=no}} Chapter 2.</ref>

由于雨水被引入下水道，地表水的自然渗透就减少了，但水流量和流速却增加了。事实上，如果大小相同，一个典型城市的不透水覆盖层阻止地表水渗入地下的能力是一个典型林地的五倍。<ref name="EPA2">U.S. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA). Washington, DC. [http://www.epa.gov/npdes/pubs/nps_urban-facts_final.pdf "Protecting Water Quality from Urban Runoff."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.epa.gov/npdes/pubs/nps_urban-facts_final.pdf |date=20180702011024 }} Document No. EPA 841-F-03-003. February 2003.</ref>

==城市径流的影响==
美国[[美國國家科學研究委員會|美國國家科學研究委員會]]在2008年的报告指出，城市径流是[[水质|水质]]污染的主要原因。<ref>United States. National Research Council. Washington, DC. [http://www.epa.gov/npdes/pubs/nrc_stormwaterreport.pdf "Urban Stormwater Management in the United States."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.epa.gov/npdes/pubs/nrc_stormwaterreport.pdf |date=20170706063459 }} October 15, 2008. pp. 18-20.</ref>

径流也使河流的温度升高，危害鱼类和其他生物。突然的暴雨径流更会导致鱼类由于水温过高而大量死亡。另外，融化道路和人行道积雪用的盐会污染河流和地下[[蓄水层|蓄水层]]。<ref>United States Geological Survey. Atlanta, GA. [http://ga.water.usgs.gov/edu/urbanrun.html "The effects of urbanization on water quality: Urban runoff."] {{Wayback|url=http://ga.water.usgs.gov/edu/urbanrun.html |date=20090610135458 }}</ref>

==预防和减少城市径流==
[[Image:Percolation_trench.jpg|thumb]]。]]
有效控制城市径流需要减少雨水的的流速和流量，并减少污染物的排放。应该利用各种雨水排放管理措施和系统来减少城市径流的影响。在美国，一些所谓的{{le|最佳管理做法|Best management practice for water pollution}}（BMPs）注重于对水量的控制，一些注重于改善水质，另一些措施則具备两种功能。<ref>EPA. [http://epa.gov/guide/stormwater/ "Preliminary Data Summary of Urban Storm Water Best Management Practices."] {{Wayback|url=http://epa.gov/guide/stormwater/ |date=20100802064730 }} Chapter 5. August 1999. Document No. EPA-821-R-99-012.</ref>

预防污染的措施包括[[低影響開發|低影響開發]]或[[綠建築|綠建築]]技术， 諸如安装[[绿化屋顶|绿化屋顶]]和改进化学处理（例如管理汽车燃料及石油、化肥和杀虫剂）。<ref>EPA. [http://cfpub.epa.gov/npdes/stormwater/menuofbmps/index.cfm?action=factsheet_results&view=specific&bmp=124 "Fact Sheet: Low Impact Development and Other Green Design Strategies."] {{Wayback|url=http://cfpub.epa.gov/npdes/stormwater/menuofbmps/index.cfm?action=factsheet_results&view=specific&bmp=124 |date=20131207202334 }} October 9, 2008.</ref> 径流减緩系统包括{{link-en|入渗池|Infiltration basin}}、{{link-en|生物滞留|Bioretention}}系统、构建湿地、保留水池和类似设施。<ref>California Stormwater Quality Association. Menlo Park, CA. [http://www.cabmphandbooks.com "Stormwater Best Management Practice (BMP) Handbooks."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cabmphandbooks.com/ |date=20080118092426 }} 2003.</ref> <ref>New Jersey Department of Environmental Protection. Trenton, NJ. [http://www.njstormwater.org/bmp_manual2.htm "New Jersey Stormwater Best Management Practices Manual."] {{Wayback|url=http://www.njstormwater.org/bmp_manual2.htm |date=20211122102819 }} April 2004.</ref>

